  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A short-trajectory to be a bankable cooperative</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increase active members of TNN from 85 to 100 farmers by 30 June 2020  Increase coffee delivered to the cooperative from 40% (146/366 tonnes) to 50% by 30 June 2020  Loan repayment to RaboFoundation (outstanding loan of 2018) : Completely repaid by 30 April 2020</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The cooperative has 106 members with 122.8 ha of coffee and 39.2 ha of pepper. Tan Nong Nguyen is providing input supply (mainly fertilizer) and access to finance by pre-financing their members for fertilizer and labor cost.  TNN is getting a loan from Rabobank Foundation with the amount of 5 billion VND (~190 000 Euro) in 2018 this has been going well over last 4 years since the establishment under support of Rabobank International Advisory Services (RIAS). RIAS is providing capacity building and trainings on cooperative model and set-up a very dynamic member involvement. The project with RIAS is coming to an end in 2019  Rabobank Foundation is requesting Agriterra to explore the potential for continuation of the support for sustainable development of Tan Nong Nguyen Cooperative.The overarching objective of the project is making TNN bankable in the short-term. A bankable cooperative implies that it has a trustworthy reputation  good management  solid linkage to the market and is able to operate efficiently. Addiionally  it is important to have a swift transition of the Technical Assistance from RIAS to Agriterra  in order to continue to provide this solid support to TNN with the objective to operate without donor support within 3-5 years (self-sustainable).BHAGThe cooperative has the ambition to increase its member to 1000 coffee growers. TNN takes the loan from Rabobank Foundation and provides microloans to its members. At the moment  TNN is facing a challenge to recover overdue and bad loans. They would like to increase internal capital from members and own sources for coffee business. TNN wants to position itself in the market as producing high quality coffee at premium price  achieve 100% loan repayment rate  and increase in internal capital. It is however having no strategic plan nor financial projection to support these ambitions.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">With the project  Agriterra will aim for the following objectives:Improve member awareness and increase amount members and amount of coffee supplied to the cooperative (Trust),Proper loan management and repayment to the RF  lsquo,pave the wayrsquo for a loan appraisal trajectory at a VN bank (Access to finance) amp self sustainablibity of the cooperative,Strengthen the capacity of board and management on governance and financial management,Provide support to the cooperative in their specific income generating activity (market linkage) Hand on training and business planning</narrative>
  </description>
